{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771247025,"nonce":"3b8tMZNMHrpJ7hronbk9M3YK6yk=","title":"Checkout borrower step has no explicit 'next step' button","message":"The checkout flow has an inconsistent navigation pattern between steps.\n\n**Step 1** (lending items): The sidebar cart has an explicit 'Verleihen' button to proceed to step 2.\n\n**Step 2** (checkout/borrower): No equivalent button exists. The only way to proceed to confirmation is clicking the arrow icon on the borrower card, which submits a form to update_checkout_path('borrower'). When a borrower is already selected (e.g. user navigated back from items), the arrow becomes a green checkmark (class 'icon in-cart'). This looks like a status indicator, not an action button, so users get stuck.\n\n**Root cause:** The sidebar cart (_sidebar_cart.html.erb) only renders action buttons when controller_name == 'lending', hiding them on checkout pages. And _result_borrower.html.erb uses the same icon for 'select borrower' and 'proceed to next step'.\n\n**Suggested fix:** Add an explicit 'Ausleihe prufen' (or 'Weiter') button to the checkout/borrower view, either in the sidebar or below the selected borrower card, visible when a borrower is already assigned to the lending. This matches the pattern of step 1 having a dedicated proceed button.","files":null}]}